parsetree.*:
<root><template><title>RV</title><part><name>type</name>=<value>command

</value></part><part><name>game1</name>=<value> arma3

</value></part><part><name>version1</name>=<value> 1.62

</value></part><part><name>gr1</name>=<value> Object Manipulation

</value></part><part><name>descr</name>=<value> Sets the minimal ASL height. Final height is <template><title>ic</title><part><name index="1"/><value>''flyInHeight'' [[max]] ''flyInHeightASL''</value></part></template> - the higher altitude has priority.

</value></part><part><name>s1</name>=<value> aircraft [[flyInHeightASL]] [standardAltitude, combatAltitude, stealthAltitude]

</value></part><part><name>p1</name>=<value> aircraft: [[Object]] - helicopter, airplane

</value></part><part><name>p2</name>=<value> standardAltitude: [[Number]] - base altitude used when [[behaviour]] is neither "COMBAT" or "STEALTH"

</value></part><part><name>p3</name>=<value> combatAltitude: [[Number]] -  altitude used when [[behaviour]] is "COMBAT"

</value></part><part><name>p4</name>=<value> stealthAltitude: [[Number]] - altitude used when [[behaviour]] is "STEALTH"

</value></part><part><name>r1</name>=<value> [[Nothing]]

</value></part><part><name>x1</name>=<value> <code>cobraOne [[flyInHeightASL]] [200, 100, 400];</code>

</value></part><part><name>seealso</name>=<value> [[flyInHeight]]
</value></part></template></root>
